main event: An unidentified object with red and flashing lights was observed in Hibbing, Minnesota, on November 9, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 6 minutes and appeared larger than a star but smaller than a plane,The observation was ground visual and the object's movement was described as up and down,There was confusion regarding whether the object was an aircraft or something else due to conflicting data,The witness reported that they have never seen an object like this before,No photographs or physical evidence were obtained.
sighted object: an unidentified object with red and flashing lights
